    <a title="Brian Harticat" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1086379-brian-harticat"><img alt="Brian Harticat" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1208295028p2/1086379.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/26789402?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brian Harticat" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brian Harticat" href="/user/show/1086379-brian-harticat">Brian Harticat</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer26789402" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10122887527190377899">Well this book took me a while to read, it&apos;s heavy reading, but I did get through it. This mouse get&apos;s a rippin&apos; bike and proceeds to kick ass. Lot&apos;s of foolin&apos; around. I do think he needed some sort of biker babe for the back seat, and maybe have some ties to a biker gang of woverines. The mouse didn&apos;t have any cool tatoos either. All in all a pretty good read.</span>
